<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFADAB0DFD338A72FBD3FD7D" pageId="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFADAB0DFD338A72FBD3FD7D" blockId="15.[707,1193,194,667]" pageId="15">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFADAB0DFD338A72FCBCFD80" bold="true" box="[731,845,593,614]" pageId="15">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFADAB0DFD2B8A48FCD0FD66" box="[707,801,619,640]" italics="true" pageId="15">apolegma</emphasis>
(= hem of a robe), a Greek noun, and refers to the widened epipleural fold.
</paragraph>
